Usage: add-wg-peer \[-y\] \[-f <file>\] \[<name> <public-key> <allowed-ips>\]
    -f <file>       systemd \.netdev file to edit
    -y              no confirmation required
    <name>          name of the peer - requires a valid hostname
    <public-key>    the PublicKey of the new peer
    <allowed-ips>   AllowedIPs of the new peer \(allows shortcut for /32 CIDR\)
  Without peer information, PublicKey and AllowedIPs will be queried interactively\.

